            . I <rs id="t18320405-154-viclabel929" type="occupation">keep the <placeName id="t18320405-154-crimeloc930">Edinburgh Castle public-house, in the New-road</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-154-crimeloc930" type="placeName" value="Edinburgh Castle public-house, in the New-road"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-154-crimeloc930" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-154-off927 t18320405-154-crimeloc930"></join>
                  </rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-154-victim1373 t18320405-154-viclabel929"></join>. The prisoner came and represented himself to me as a <rs id="t18320405-154-deflabel931" type="occupation">servant out of place</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-154-defend1371 t18320405-154-deflabel931"></join>; he lodged with me for a fortnight, in a room on the first floor. On Saturday night, the 31st of March, my wife said she heard some person in our bed-room, as we were sitting down stairs; I went up, and found no one there, but I saw one of the drawers had been opened - I went into the room in which the prisoner slept, and he was concealed under the bed; I said, "Who is here?" he turned his head, and I said, "It is you, is it? I did not expect to see you here - I thought you were a respectable man;" he said, "Pray forgive me;" I said,"I can't, I have been robbed several times" - I brought him down, and a person searched him, and found the gold pins, the ring, key, and seal, which were attached together, and the brooch; they had all been taken from a little box in my room - the other things were under the bed where I found him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-154-person1375">
